	   <a name=98572950214407></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98572950214407><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98572950214407>Crowd Control Problems</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98572950214407#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=38139><span id= >Aethyrs</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 27th 4:45 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a 40th Necro that is in need of some expert advice.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do know that I am not a an enchanter and will fail terribly compared to an enchanter at crowd control. However, many times I will be the closest thing to a crowd controller as there is.<br><br>I am running into 2 problems that you guys may have a solution for.<br><br>Situation:  The group puller pulls a train of Icebone Skeletons (3) to our group.  Everyone says to assist puller...everyone proceeds to bash 1st creature.  Enchanter or myself...root or mezz..or charm or screaming terror(mezz) the other 2.  Wait till first one dies..and move on to next one..etc..<br><br><br>Problem One:<br><br>Assisting.  If everyone assists, one creature will be targeted...leaves the other two for mezzing...etc.  What I am finding is that I will have to get extremely close to the puller, so when I hit assist, it will target the correct monster.  This will give all three of the GIB's a chance to hit me.  If that happens, my pet will jump in and attack the one who hit me...  so it may or may not be the correct target.  So now we have at least 2 skeles that are engaged in melee..<br><br>Problem 2<br><br>How do u select monsters in a very confined space.  I have an assist key...see problem #1.. I also have a select closest npc key (if i use it may or may not be the correct monster that is either supposed to be attacked or mezzed.  So u move closer, just to realiz that all three of the skeletons are moving as one beast and u try to click on the one that is not being bashed on...god only knows which one u select..now Im too close...see problem #1..or I take a chance and cast screaming terror..he resists..see problem 1...  <br><br>Ack...any advice would be greatly appreciated.<br><br>Thanks!<br>Aethyrs<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
