<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99076687961700></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99076687961700><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99076687961700>RE: Crowd Control Problems</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99076687961700#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 25th 1:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry, but I find AE mez sloppy and ineffecive.&nbsp;&nbsp;Up to lvl 52, your AE only lasts 16 seconds.  16 seconds is not enough to get anything else done.  At 49+ you can Dazzle, that lasts 96 seconds.  I single target, always, unless I'm raiding green con mobs.  It takes skill and practice, you have to learn to click in the exact spot to get the right mob, and if you can't do that, walk right up to the fight and color flux 'em.  That usually gets the unmezed ones rooted out.  Good tanks know how to split pulls up, but if they can't you can.  Another dirty little trick...clerics tend to attract unmezed mobs, they have decent ac too, so sometimes, if nothing else, the cleric accidentally splits em for you.<br><br>Tarnin Austa, 52 enchanter<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
