	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmm..this question has alot of correct answers and no real wrong ones.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am currently lvl 54 and I rarely use AE Mez anymore.  Instead I learned from about 20 on that by takeing a few seconds to let the tanks do some dmg to a mob it becomes much easier to seperate mobs. Also it makes it much easier to tell when people arent assisting&lt;you will preach on this subject all your life&gt;, &lt;when pets arent undercontrol, my other pet peeve&gt;<br><br>Trick is your tanks need to understand you have it undercontrol.  Through useing this technique the tanks will come to trust that you will do everything in your power to keep them alive.  You need that degree of trust between your tanks and you.  You also have to feel the exact same about your cleric.  Running wround the room screaming becuase you cant get a mez to stick and the mob is killing you will get you killed.  Calmly stand your ground.  Continue to attempt to mez the mob and wait for the tank/cleric to save your woosey butt.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
