	   <tr><td colspan=2>I use techniques based on who I'm playing with.<br><br>If I solo:<br>Buff me and my pet (or charm)<br>Mez the mob<br>Tashan<br>Debuff (Enfeeble)<br>Languid Pace<br>DOT<br>When the monster hits 1st time,<br>Back up,<br>Whirl Till you hurl<br>Meelee until it wears off<br>Backup <br>DOT<br>Whirl<br>Rinse and repeat<br><br>For groups I often use the same thing unless grouping with Druids in which case if your in the open:<br>Mez, Tash, Dot, Get Hit, Backup, Fear<br>Druid should Snare right after Tash<br><br>Then just run along behind and whack.&nbsp;&nbsp;I partner with a druid and we rarely take ANY damage on yellows (besides the first whack).<br><br>Always use whatever buffs/debuffs you have.  They are FANTASTIC.  Groups will love you, when they start to notice, loosing fewer hit points, easier kills, faster pulling.  Enchanters RULE!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
