	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am now an 18th lvl enchanter. I found it rather annoying to not be able to group when I was first starting out so I picked up 2 handed blunt right away so I could defend myself. I spent alot of time by the castle in Gfay just fighting bats, wasps, skeketons and orc pawns. Once I got out of that and near Orc hill, I would first Mez or root, then I would use suffocating sphere, sometimes I could get that off twice, otherwise I pounded with my staff. Sometimes I died. It happens! I finally found myself a good group . . and enchanters like clerics, need GOOD groups, someone who will protect them at all costs. I was lucky to find mine. Now I am in High keep, and feel quite the same as I did when starting out . .useless, except for Breezeing everyone in sight and binding. I gain my exp from everyone elses kill in the groupe cause I can't do anything. The pickclaws resist everything I have.Including my breath spells! But, I'm still having fun. I don't get to play often cause I have a 3 yr old toddler in real life. But I have had the character since Nov. and she is now 18th. So my advice is to really build up that combat skill, root first and then let them have it with everything you've got! If they still come after you . . RUN like heck. Then, find a good group!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
