	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have to agree that item procs ofte leave something to be desired... but they are designed for a non-twink world. I got my Staff of Writhing at level 22, and it finally started to proc at level 28. It casts our level 8 DD (48hp dmg), which is not spectacular, but can be very helpful. When I'm soloing with a pet, the proc is great at aggroing the MOB back to me when the pet is getting beat down... and it's also great for runners.<br><br>I get a lot of looks from people when they see an Enchanter with a Staff of Writhing. They think that because of the -9 CHA, no Enchanter would ever use it. Well, in groups that would be very true, but if you're not mezzing/charming your CHA doesn't matter all that much.<br><br>One last thing, if you're going to use a proccing item, get your DEX as high as possible, as that will increase the number of times the item will proc. I suggest getting a pair of Electrum Star Ruby rings (+7 CHA/+5 DEX) from the nearest jeweler... they are fabulous!! (buy them from me!!!)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
