	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 25th 1:10 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok first off, there is no excuse to NOT have 200 charisma, its insanely easy to raise, the items are dirt cheap (i mean 200 buffed, like 160ish unbuffed).&nbsp;&nbsp;1 resist on a mez can be your life in many situations, and, as they say, better safe than sorry.  Second, someone mentioned that they're never full mana.  That's not the case for me.  You move into a camp full mana.  And breaking a camp is when enchanters are most needed, you want every drop of mana you can get in case things go bad.  AFK pullers or whatnot can bring little pull breaks, you'll fill back up eventually.  As a little side note, get to lvl 51, get Theft of Thought, go to sebilis.  Like 50% of the mobs there are casters, and ToT will give half a bubble to a bubble of mana, depending on your max mana pool every 2 minutes.  Groups I'm in pull 2-3 frogs at a time, I mez them, keep tanks hasted and casters buffed, and am Rarely below 75% mana.  I guess the point is, you need your mana pool to be as big as you can for emergencies, and you need your charisma to be max (i think 200 is the soft cap, not sure though) to avoid emergencies.  Then go AC and Agi, I take a beating cause mine still suck =p<br><br>Tarnin Austa, Illusionist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
