	   <tr><td colspan=2>Charisma effects the enchanters charm line, their mez line , and some effect on stun.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is about all of the things an enchanter is best at, and pretty well defines your job.  As an enchanter you are seldom OOM anyway. So the extra mana from Int is not that big a help.  Most of the people playing enchanters that claim you need high Int are playing enchanters like wizards.  If you think you want to cast a lot of DD spells then start a wizard.  As an enchanter you are there to reduce death count, control over pulls, and turn that train into a huge exp windfall(charm)... All of those things are accomplished by spells that are directly effected by charisma.  <br><br>As for how well charisma effects spells.  At 120 cha charm will stick, but not every time and did not last long.  At 160 charisma I could charm stuff higher level than me and hold them for most of a battle.  At 200 cha, I can charm something red almost everytime, and hold it for most of a battle, and recharm with little or no trouble.  <br><br>Besides, Int and Cha are two of the easiest to raise with items.  so you should be aiming at 200/200... But I would definately spend the point in Cha in character creation.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
