	   <a name=98642955175381></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98642955175381><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98642955175381>RE: how do you do the stein of moggok quest what do you need</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98642955175381#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 4th 8:12 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The information that you are about to recieve will be the best that is curently available.<br><br>I do not take credit for the writing of the spoiler, this was found on evelore.com and<br>the locs were found on eqvault.com<br><br>I only take credit for the research.<br><br>I have done this quest 7 times this weekend using the curent information that will be listed below.<br><br>The way that I do this quest is by running most of it, and only using one TP to N.Karana to start the quest.<br><br>I find that my technique is the most econmical, but not the most time eficiant.<br>The quest takes me between 2 hrs to 2 1/2 hrs to complete this way.<br>If you have TP's you can do this a lot quicker.<br><br>Please print this out, and read it completly.<br>I promise you that this quest will be no problem.<br><br>At the end of this I will give you my routing that I run this quest.<br><br>I hope this helps.<br>If you dont know how to use your Loc, now is a good time to learn.<br>The Information Starts Here.<br>-------------------------------<br>Nearly everyone who wrote about this quest up to this point is confusing and unclear. Here is how to obtain the Stein of Moggok, whose main effect is the +10 to Intelligence:<br><br>1) Hail Barkeep Gregor in the tavern to the left of the dock in Eastern Freeport. He will tell you to bring him a Kiola Nut, a Honey Jum, a Koalindl Fish, and an Erud's Tonic.<br><br>2) Bind yourself at the docks, take the ship to the Island of Errollisi (Sister Isle), buy a Kiola Nut (or several, for it is the only non-Lore Item of the Quest), and Gate back. Or you can take the ship all the way around if you wish.<br><br>3) Go to Rivervale (through East Freeport, West Freeport, East Commons, West Commons, and Kithicor Forest [travel through it by day only, lest you be slain by horrible undead]) Get 3 Honey Combs. Merchants often have them from people's sales, you can auction for them (preferrably in Misty Thicket), or you can hunt some Bixie Drones, which often drop Honey Combs. Give 3 Honey Combs and 30 Gold to a Merchant in Rivervale named Kizzie. She will give you a Honey Jum.<br><br>4) Go to Qeynos (through Kithicor Forest, High Pass, East Karana, North Karana, West Karana, and Qeynos Hills). There, in the pool in the Temple of Life, Koalindl Fishes exist. The faction hit from killing them is very bad, so you migh want to hire a newbie to kill them for you (they are Level 1), though make sure that they do not loot it, since the item is No Drop. Another way of getting a Koalindl is killing a dog named Frostbite (In North Karana, I believe) owned by a Barbarian.<br><br>5)Next go to Erudin; Binding yourself in Qeynos is a good idea. Take the ship at the docks of South Qeynos across Erud's Crossing. In Erudin, take a teleporter into the city itself from the building by the docks. Find the Blue Hawk Tavern, and purchase an Innoruuk's Kiss Of Death. Go to the Library of Erudin, taking the stair up. You will see a female NPC with the second name Highbrow. Hail her, and she will tell you that she likes reading and is considered a bookworm (if you ask the barkeep about Erud's Tonic, he will tell you to give the Bookworm a Kiss). Give her the Innoruuk's Kiss of Death and she will give you Erud's Tonic.<br><br>6)Gate back to Qeynos and return to East Freeport. Cast Illusion: Human on yourself and Alliance on Gregor and give him the four items one by one. He will give you a Barkeep's Compendium, saying that it is magically sealed, but that its original owner, an Ogre named Clurg, might reward you for it.<br><br>7) Bind yourself in Freeport and go to Oggok (through Eastern Freeport, North Ro, Oasis of Marr, South Ro, Innothule Swamp, and Feerrott). Make sure to wear the Illusion of a Dark Elf or another Darkie (through the whole trip to Oggok if you are on a PvP server) and also invisibility. At the far end of Oggok, in the caves, there is a tavern called Meet And Drink Tew Bie. Clurg is there. Making sure to keep a Darkie illusion, cast Alliance on him and give him the Compendium. It will get you some experience and platinum, while raising various Ogre factions and lowering your faction with Kazon Stormhammer, the king of Dwarves. And he gives you the Stein of Moggok. Then Gate back to Freeport and bask in relief (especially if you are on a PvP server).<br><br><br>The Stein can be sold to casters for 200-350 platinum, though being a Lore Item, only one can be held at a time. If you want a headstart on getting another Stein, keep your bind in Qeynos while finishing the quest, though you will be risking a long walk if you die. But it'll save you half of your journey if you succeed. Of course, teleports and such will make the quest easier and getting Spirit of the Wold for the long runs across the Commonlands and Karanas is definitely a plaus (make sure to get directions, too). That is all. May you be well!<br><br>This is the Loc guide.<br><br>Beholder Runnyeye Zone = 900, -1800 E Karana Zone = -1200, -500 <br>Xorbb's Altar = -500, 600 <br><br><br> <br>Butcher Block Mountains Kaladim = 2900, -200 Dagnor's Cauldron Zone = -2700, -400 <br>Crossroads = -1000, 50 Chessboard = 900, -2700 <br>Smeltpot Bandits = -500, -600 Faydark Zone = -1100, -3000 <br>Docs = 1350, 2400 OOT Zone = 1100, 3000 <br>Druid Ring = -2150, 2100 Dwarf Bandits = -200, 1650 <br>Goblin Camp I = 2100, -1800 Goblin Camp II = -2150, -200 <br>Goblin Camp III = -300, -2100 Goblin Warriors = -200, 1650 <br>Orcs = 350, -1600 <br><br><br>Crushbone Faydark Zone = -650, 150 Castle = 0, 0&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br><br>Dagnor's Cauldron Unrest Zone= -1600, -700 Kedge Keep Zone = -1000, -1000 <br>Butcherblock Zone = 2650, 250 Dena Rod = -900, -750 <br><br><br>East Commons Tunnel to NRo = -775, 775 Nektulos Zone = 1300, 800  <br>West Commons Zone = 0, 5000 West Freeport Zone = 0, -1400  <br>Orc Camp I = 900, 2700 Orc Camp II = 900, 4600  <br>Inn I = 950, 3650 Inn II = -150, 100  <br>Inn III = -250, 3000 Inn IV = 250, 4850  <br>Ruins = -850, 2800  <br><br><br>East Karana Ramp to HH = -350, -3150 Barbarian Village = -3900, -1500 <br>Wooden Bridge (NK Zone) = 0, 850 Beholder Guards = 1600, -2500 <br>King Xorbb's Maze = 3600, -2000 HH Zone = -3000, -7900 <br>Gnoll Reavers = -3200, 200 <br><br><br>Erud's Crossing S Qeynos Zone = 400, 1100 Azia Rod = -1150, 2350 <br><br><br>Everfrost Peaks Permafrost Zone = 1900, -6400 Blackburrow Zone = -2500, 300 <br>Tinter = 2000, 500 Evercave = 3100, -3900 <br>Beza Rod = 5000, -5000 Hole in Water = 1300, -4500 <br>Goblins = -1000, -1500 Halas Zone = 3100, 600 <br>Shaman Temple = 2500, -3500 Watchtower = 2000, -3700 <br>3 Igloos = 100, 1000 Perma Side Entrance = 3200, -6300 <br><br><br>Fear Entrance = -1000, 1000 Scareling Tower = -1300, 500 <br>Dread = -700, -400 Fright = 100, -400 <br>Terror = -800, -1200 Temple = 800, 400 <br>Graveyard = 400, 40 Gorgon Shrine = -500, -80 <br>Chapel = 1200,  Bell Tower = 100, 0 <br><br><br>Feerrott Cazic Thule Zone = -1400, 100 Oggok Zone = 1500, 900 <br>Rathe Mtns Zone = 500, 3000 Innothule Zone = -1000, -3075 <br>Fear Zone = -1450, 2700 Druid Ring = 350, -1800 <br>Vendor = 1150, 100  <br><br><br>Greater Faydark Felwithe Zone = -2000, -2400 Wizard Portal = -2000, 400 <br>Butcherblock Zone = -1500, 2500 Crushbone Zone = 2400, 0 <br>Lesser Fay Zone = -2500, -1000 Orc Lift = 1000, 200 <br>PoD Lift = 150, 200 Newbie Lift = 0, -100 <br>Orc Hill = 1850, -100 Orc Camps = 1750, -150 <br>Bandit Camp = -1250, -700 Ruins = 450, -400 <br><br><br>High Hold Pass E Karana Zone = 850, 100 Kithicor Zone = -950, 150 <br>HH Keep = -100, -100 <br><br><br>Innothule Swamp Guk = 200, -700 Grobb = -2700, -500 <br>Feerrott Zone = -1000, 1800 South Ro Zone = 2400, 1000 <br><br><br>Kithicor Woods W Commons Zone = 1400, -1050 High Hold Zone = 400, 4800 <br>Ranger Guild = 1400, 2300 Rivervale Zone = 1900, 3800 <br><br><br>La