	   <tr><td colspan=2>The only thing worse than having to explain yourself as an enchanter, is when a member or two decides to curse you out on group chat for being bossy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thing is it's extremely hard to have everyone get on the same page and "gently" explain to them why they need to listen to the enchanter.  On the flip side, once you get into a group where everyone had the assist key, and is on the same target, it's like a dream come true.  Simply keep the tanks hasted and your Casters Breezed/Claritied and med the rest of the time.  If things are really bad, your probably better off trying to find a new group.  On a bad night, I found I was wasting my whole night trying to get back to 0.  Never mind about making Xp.  Ask the group if they have assist, if there not using it, or cursing you out (I've experienced that a couple of times)  just offer to leave.  You'll be better off in the end, and be less frustrated.  Oh yah, and once oyu do find those "smart" players make sure you write their names down for future reference.   :o)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
