	   <a name=98581179935379></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98581179935379><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98581179935379>RE: Looking for some GOOD advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98581179935379#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 28th 3:36 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's what I've noticed, and this may or may not work in all situations, but it works in most.<br><br>/Assist is essential for this tactic, for the obvious and for reasons I will describe.<br><br>Here's how this tactic works:&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, when your tanks are pounding a mob, they are constantly pushing this mob backwards.  Also, the mob that is not being hacked on is pushing closer to your tank.  This makes for an interesting situation.  If you stand directly behind your puller and hit F8 you are GUARANTEED to hit the mob that is closer to you, which is also the one that is NOT being pushed away by the tank.  If the rest of the group is using /assist, you will hit the right mob using F8 100% of the time.  now if you are off center to the side, this tactic may not help.  Also, if you are IN FRONT of your tanks, you will hit the mob that is being pushed back 100% of the time. (great for rogues btw).  The key to this is patience, you have to wait until the tank stops moving.<br><br>If there are 3 mobs in the pack, F8 mez one then the tank backs up and 2 will follow, the one that is being pounded gets pushed back again, mez second, tank backs up again and the 3 mobs are spaced out and easy targets.  WORKS all the time as long as you stay DIRECTLY BEHIND your tank.<br><br>Hope this helps some of you out some, I know it has saved my life a few times.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
