	   <tr><td colspan=2>HI there,<br>I like the post from the guy above me, as for the first time id have to probably agree with all or at least most of what he said.<br>Yes Chanters can be a bit "hmmm so when do i get good then" at low level, but at high lev or even after mid 20s you fall into your own.<br>On many raids ie vox for example v a big powerfull nastie chanters are used to Mass drain the manna from an enemy to eradicate a bad aspect of it.<br>For example V vox she has a habbit of TOTAL HEALING herself ina battle and with over 30000 hp that SUCKS bad. If she gets it off its offen prety much OVER.<br>However with mass manna draining she can be reduced to no manna, making it just a big hack fest for the buffed tanks.<br>A note on charm:<br>I wouldnt say DONT charm, id say be prepared to use it only if the tide of battle is slipping and having an extra tank on your side and one less on theres can save the battle.<br>Sometimes in a bad situation..usually with some FOOL who loves his AE DD to much it is the only thing that saves your life.<br>I found that out in paw around lev 30.<br>TRUE at higher lev though, if some one working in a group with an Enchie DOES AE DD he needs booting from the group, because he will kill a group as sure as the mobs can.<br><br>I have been told in the past I am obviously LYING when i say that at lev 36 I could solo the whole spectre tower in oasis.<br>Its good to see that someone else CAN also do that and that its just a hard to master but GREAT tactic.<br>I dont know another class that could do that except US enchies.<br>I would say though , dont get to happy with yourself if you do master it, because theres very few places or levels that you can use the tactic to great effect.<br>Oasis just happens to have lots of room, water to help slow the mob as you retreat, and a good number of mobs to handel.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
